<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
  Sample PG&E Share My Data (Green Button / ESPI) export for ONE account holding
  THREE service IDs (a multi-meter account): Sandhu Family Farms' Home Ranch Well,
  North Well, and River Well. Built to the published NAESB ESPI / Atom schema so
  the parser is unchanged when real Self-Access data flows later.

  Structure: an Atom <feed> of <entry> elements, each wrapping one ESPI resource
  in <content>, linked by <link rel="self|up|related"> hrefs under
  .../UsagePoint/{serviceId}/... paths. Per UsagePoint: one MeterReading + one
  ReadingType (units), two IntervalBlocks (one per billing cycle of 15-minute
  IntervalReadings), two UsageSummary entries (tariff + demand charge per cycle),
  and one ServiceLocation (address).

  Conventions (see fixtures/greenbutton/README.md):
  - Interval <value> is energy in the ReadingType's uom (72 = Wh) scaled by
    powerOfTenMultiplier: kWh = value * 10^mult / 1000. Home Ranch and North use
    mult 0 (Wh); River uses mult 3 (kWh) to exercise the scaler.
  - Monetary fields (billLastPeriod, LineItem amount) are in 1/100,000 of the
    currency: 201600000 = $2,016.00.
  - Demand charge = LineItems whose note matches /demand/i. AG-C cycles carry both
    a Maximum Demand Charge and a Summer Peak Demand Charge; AG-B carries only the
    Maximum Demand Charge (AG-C adds the summer peak demand charge).
  - Interval series are abbreviated to a representative afternoon cluster per cycle
    with one engineered peak, so tests assert exact kW. A real feed has ~2,880
    intervals per cycle; the parser handles any count.
-->
<feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:espi="http://naesb.org/espi">
